com.poesys.db.dao.insert

Class InsertCacheFactory<T extends IDbDto,C extends java.util.Collection<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dao.insert.InsertFactory<T>
      • com.poesys.db.dao.insert.InsertCacheFactory<T,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the database DTO type to insert
    C - the type of collection of DTOs to insert

    public class InsertCacheFactory<T extends IDbDto,C extends java.util.Collection<T>>
extends InsertFactory<T>
    The InsertCacheFactory lets you generate an insert object appropriate to your desired insert framework. This class subclasses the general InsertFactory and generates objects that insert objects into the database and into an in-memory cache. Use the InsertFactory class to insert the objects directly into the database without caching.
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller
